sentences: Johnny Dollar (March 8, 1933 – April 13, 1986) was an American country and rockabilly musician.
Dollar relocated to Dallas in the early 1950s, where he worked in trucking and in a lumber yard.
In 1952 he recorded a single for D Records, but it was not successful, and Dollar then found work as a DJ in Louisiana and New Mexico.
There he began fronting a group called the Texas Sons and performed on the Louisiana Hayride in the middle of the 1950s.
In 1964, he met Ray Price, and this encounter led to a contract with Columbia Records.

His best-selling album was 1968's Johnny Dollar, which reached No. 41 on the U.S. Billboard Country Albums chart.
